PublicationLoa.description: On lines 15-21 we create our SPARQL CONSTRUCT-query. The only real difference is line 17, where we use a CONSTRUCT-clause (instead of the SELECT-clause we saw previously). Line 23 turns the query string into a prepared Query object. Since the result of a CONSTRUCT-query is a set of RDF statements (in other words: a graph), RDF4J calls such a query a GraphQuery , and its result a GraphQueryResult .
